results.name: Number of primes with prime subscripts dividing n.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..5000
example: a(15) = 2 because 15 has 4 divisors {1,3,5,15} among which 2 divisors {3,5} are primes with prime subscripts.
program: (PARI) x='x+O('x^120); concat([0, 0], Vec(sum(k=1, 120, x^prime(prime(k))/(1 - x^prime(prime(k)))))) \\ _Indranil Ghosh_, May 23 2017
